column5: Hi all, Got out for some walleye yesterday afternoon, not much happened for 3 hours until a brief window of opportunity opened as the sun hit the tree line, beautiful sunny day, only around -3C and despite a fairly stiff wind I was well sheltered on my chosen spot. Bite lasted 20 minutes or so before it switched off ass quickly as it started.
Timing is everything lol...Â  nice feed.
Another great little escape I appreciate you sharing with us
Hence the phrase, being in the right place at the right time. Very nice, good goin.
